The paper focuses on convolutional neural networks (CNN) and their hardware acceleration, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the reduction of computational and memory requirements, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper presents a framework for hardware-oriented approximation, which is related to system and control (cs.SY) research.
